run.signature: export function run<T>(contextObject: OfficeExtension.ClientRequestContext, batch: (context: Visio.RequestContext) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>;

description.text: A previously-created Visio.RequestContext. This context will get re-used by the batch function (instead of having a new context created). This means that the batch will be able to pick up changes made to existing API objects, if those objects were derived from this same context.

A function that takes in a RequestContext and returns a promise (typically, just the result of "context.sync()"). The context parameter facilitates requests to the Visio application. Since the Office add-in and the Visio application run in two different processes, the RequestContext is required to get access to the Visio object model from the add-in.

summary.text: Executes a batch script that performs actions on the Visio object model, using the RequestContext of a previously-created object. When the promise is resolved, any tracked objects that were automatically allocated during execution will be released.
